df = df[df.Omit!='not a good image'] # remove rows where Omit=='not a good image'

All Patients¶

In [9]:
unique_patients = np.unique(df['Patient'])

for location in locations:
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 5), dpi=150)
    for quantity in quantities:
        plt.subplot(1, len(quantities), quantities.index(quantity) + 1)

        data_to_plot = []
        labels = []
        for patient in unique_patients:
            df_where = df[df['Where'] == location]
            df_patient = df_where[df_where['Patient'] == patient]

            data_to_plot.append(df_patient[quantity])
            labels.append(f'{patient}')

        plt.boxplot(data_to_plot, labels=labels)
        plt.xlabel('Patient')
        plt.ylabel(quantity)
        plt.title('Location = ' + location + '\n' + quantity)

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

    • 005
    • 009
  • Mod-severe fat, yes fibrosis (red)

    • 020 (stage 4)

All patients, ordered and colored by fat, fibrosis¶

In [19]:
custom_order = ['7', '41', '21', '3', '5', '9', '16', '20']
In [20]:
patient_colors = {
    7: 'xkcd:pale green',
    41: 'xkcd:pale green',
    3: 'xkcd:pale yellow',
    17: 'xkcd:pale yellow',
    21: 'xkcd:pale yellow',
    5: 'xkcd:light orange',
    9: 'xkcd:light orange',
    16: 'xkcd:salmon',
    20: 'xkcd:salmon'
}

for location in locations:
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 5), dpi=150)
    for quantity in quantities:
        plt.subplot(1, len(quantities), quantities.index(quantity) + 1)

        data_to_plot = []
        labels = []
        for patient in custom_order:
            patient_id = ''.join(filter(str.isdigit, patient))
            df_where = df[df['Where'] == location]
            df_patient = df_where[df_where['Patient'] == int(patient_id)]

            data_to_plot.append(df_patient[quantity])
            labels.append(patient)

        boxplot = plt.boxplot(data_to_plot, labels=labels, patch_artist=True, medianprops={'color': 'black'})

        for i, patient in enumerate(custom_order):
            patient_id = ''.join(filter(str.isdigit, patient))
            box = boxplot['boxes'][i]
            box.set_facecolor(patient_colors.get(int(patient_id), 'white'))

        plt.xlabel('Patient')
        plt.ylabel(quantity)
        plt.title('Location = ' + location + '\n' + quantity)
        plt.xticks(range(1, len(custom_order) + 1), custom_order, rotation=45, ha='right')

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
